      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1613595016,
      "post_id" : 25734955,
      "comment_id" : 117126749,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "If I understand what you&#39;re asking .... the answer is no. The name of the environment variable should be exactly the same  in the pom as it is declared in the OS. So, transforming underscores for dots is a NO NO."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1590699,
      "reputation" : 3444,
      "user_id" : 1474069,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 80,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/80dd5f76d4f164348c5ec1f263a2da4b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
