    "question_id" : 10463077,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>It might be safer to directly pass environment variables to Maven system properties. For example, say on Linux you want to access environment variable <code>MY_VARIABLE</code>. You can use a system property in your POM file.</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;properties&gt;\n    ...\n    &lt;!-- Default value for my.variable can be defined here --&gt;\n    &lt;my.variable&gt;foo&lt;/my.variable&gt;\n    ...\n&lt;/properties&gt;\n...\n&lt;!-- Use my.variable --&gt;\n... ${my.variable} ...\n</code></pre>\n<p>Set the property value on the Maven command line:</p>\n<pre><code>mvn clean package -Dmy.variable=$MY_VARIABLE\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
